---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import site from '../../site.config.json';
const c = site.colours;
---
<BaseLayout title="Printix vs PaperCut -- Cloud Print Management Comparison" description="Compare Printix and PaperCut for cloud print management. Feature comparison, architecture differences, and pricing models for Australian organisations.">
  <section class="section-pad">
    <div class="container" style="max-width:800px">
      <p class="eyebrow">COMPARE</p>
      <h1 style="font-size:clamp(28px,4vw,42px);font-weight:800;margin-bottom:16px">Printix vs PaperCut</h1>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:40px">Both Printix and PaperCut offer print management capabilities, but they take fundamentally different approaches to architecture and deployment. This comparison may help organisations evaluate which approach suits their environment.</p>
      <div class="comparison-table-wrap">
        <table class="comparison-table">
          <thead><tr><th>Feature</th><th>Printix</th><th>PaperCut</th></tr></thead>
          <tbody>
            <tr><td>Architecture</td><td>Cloud-native, serverless</td><td>Server-based (on-premise or cloud-hosted)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Print servers required</td><td>No</td><td>Yes (PaperCut MF/NG require a server)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Management interface</td><td>Cloud web dashboard</td><td>Web admin on local server</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Driver management</td><td>Cloud driver store, automated</td><td>Manual or scripted driver deployment</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Secure print release</td><td>App, QR code, NFC, ID badge</td><td>ID badge, PIN, NFC (varies by product)</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Remote / home printing</td><td>Built-in, no VPN required</td><td>Requires VPN or additional configuration</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Platform support</td><td>Windows, Mac, Chromebook, iOS, Android</td><td>Windows, Mac, Linux, Chromebook</td></tr>
            <tr><td>SSO integration</td><td>Entra ID, Google, Okta, OneLogin</td><td>Active Directory, LDAP</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Scan/capture</td><td>Built-in with OCR</td><td>Available in PaperCut MF</td></tr>
            <tr><td>Pricing model</td><td>Per-user subscription (all features)</td><td>Per-device licensing (varies by product tier)</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <h2 style="margin-top:40px;margin-bottom:16px">Key differences</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px">The most significant architectural difference is that Printix eliminates print servers entirely. Configuration, policy, and reporting live in the cloud, while print data stays on the local network. PaperCut products typically require an on-premise server for core functionality.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px">Organisations that prioritise removing server infrastructure and simplifying IT operations may find the Printix approach more aligned with their strategy. Organisations with existing PaperCut deployments and invested server infrastructure may prefer to continue with that platform.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="line-height:1.7;margin-bottom:16px">Printix includes all features at every pricing tier, with volume discounts based on user count. PaperCut offers multiple product tiers (Hive, Pocket, MF, NG) with different feature sets at different price points.</p>
      <p class="muted" style="font-size:13px;margin-top:32px;font-style:italic">This comparison is based on publicly available information as of March 2026. Features and pricing may change. Verify current details with each vendor before making purchasing decisions.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
  <section class="section-pad section-dark" style="padding:60px 0">
    <div class="container text-center">
      <h2 style="margin-bottom:12px">Try Printix free for 30 days</h2>
      <p class="muted" style="margin-bottom:24px">All features included. No credit card required.</p>
      <div style="display:flex;gap:12px;justify-content:center;flex-wrap:wrap"><a href={site.hero.ctaPrimaryUrl} class="btn-primary">Start free trial</a><a href="/contact" class="btn-secondary" style="border-color:rgba(255,255,255,0.3);color:#fff">Request a quote</a></div>
    </div>
  </section>
  <style is:inline>
    .eyebrow{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--brand);letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:12px}
    .comparison-table-wrap{overflow-x:auto}.comparison-table{width:100%;border-collapse:collapse;font-size:14px}.comparison-table th,.comparison-table td{padding:12px 16px;text-align:left;border-bottom:1px solid var(--border)}.comparison-table th{font-weight:600;font-size:13px;color:var(--muted);text-transform:uppercase;letter-spacing:0.04em;background:var(--neutral)}
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
